    "body": "Ah yes, this is kind of a known limitation for now. `~` and environment variable expansion are shell specific stuff, so they are expanded by your shell, not geth. The values in the config files are flat strings. We did have a short discussion whether this could be a useful feature to add.\r\n\r\nI'll ping @fjl for his feedback.",
